TASKS COMPLETED : Study of CODR-OBDH

Topics Studied:
1. Hardware components: General hardware design and types of architecture.
2. Parameters for component selection.
3. Radiation effects- bit flips and latch up errors.
4. Constituents of a processor and its architecture- Von-Neumann and Harvard, classification of processors- CISC,RISC and DSP.
5. Classification and choice of memory,type of data to be stored, memory management and interfacing.
6. Serial and parallel modes of communication, basic knowledge of I2C,SPI and UART.
7. Features of a microcontroller and software components.
